  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6819.72 sitting right between massive negative gamma at 6810 (-52.7B) and positive gamma resistance at 6830 (+33.7B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy any dips toward 6810 and sell any push toward 6830. The breakout regime with -55B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves, but the proximity to max positive gamma at 6830 creates a natural ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies. Watch for violent whipsaws between 6810-6830 as dealers flip between buying and selling modes within this tight 20-point range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves but capped near 6830 with strong support at 6810.",
